nt of the business of horticulture in the first decades of the nineteenth century -- the practices of importers, merchants, farms, and households -- placing it within the broader context of social history. It includes an appendix of historic sites and botanical gardens in Ontario, as well as sources for heritage seeds. Early Canadian Gardening is a ground-breaking account of the practice and significance of horticulture during the period of settlement in Upper Canada and stands as a remarkable work of historical botany. It will be an invaluable source document for horticulturists and botanists, historians, and garden enthusiasts with an interest in heritage plants.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBotaniquexSourcesxHistoirexOntario. 0aBotanyxHistoryxOntario. 0aBotanyzOntarioxHistoryvSources. 0aBotanyzOntarioxHistory. 0aGardeningxSourcesxHistoryx19th centuryxOntario. 0aGardeningzOntarioxHistoryy19th centuryvSources. 0aHorticulturexSourcesxHistoirex19e sièclexOntario. 0aHorticulturexSourcesxHistoryx19th centuryxOntario. 0aHorticulturezOntarioxHistoryy19th centuryvSources. 0aJardinagexSourcesxHistoirex19e sièclexOntario. 0aNursery stockvCatalogs. 0aNursery stockxCatalogs. 0aProduits de pépinièresxCataloguesxOntario. 7aGARDENING / Techniques.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356721440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773567214423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773567214/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter